feeling of happiness and with memories of good times.  The ragefire spawn though leaves one to log off feeling bitter, disgusted and completly frustrated with the game.  Because of this I want to try to fix the situation.  I am asking that all players send an email to the following addresses to let verant know that we are not happy with the ending of the cleric epic.  <br><br><br><br>mailto:eqfeedback@soe.sony.com<br><br>mailto:eqmail@soe.sony.com<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>  If you want you can just copy and paste the following to your email.<br><br>  I am a player of Everquest.  I am asking the designers at Verant to please come up with a better solution for the ending of the cleric epic.  The current spawn rate and accessibilty of Ragefire causes contention and fights among people that normaly are friends.  It is my belief that the spirit of the game is something that wants us to work together and to interact with others.  Ragefire as he now is designed almost forces players to go against each other and leads to bitter feelings for everyone.  Please consider the situation as it now stands and look for a solution that will not pit friends against friends.  Thank you for your time and have a good day.<br><br><br><br><br><br>  I do not know if Verant will listen to us or not, but I do know that I feel we must try to do something.  The way things are now with Ragefire simply stink.  More then one person I know says the camp is painful and wish something would be done about it.  Well now is the time for us to try to do something about it.  This message is being posted on as many boards as I can find that are related to Everquest.  Let your friends know and have them send Verant an email.  If nothing else is done atleast we will have voiced our opinons and have tried to fix the problem as best we can.  Thank you all for your time and may you have good hunting and safe journies.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20